title: Moonfish
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, International, Organic, Western, Beer/Wine, Take-out, Fusion, Guatemalan, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Mostly (previously all) vegetarian spot specializing in tempeh and tofu dishes, with a few meat dishes included in the menu. Well-known in town for their tofu scrambles, burritos, falafel, and fresh salads. Made-in-house peanut, spicy, and yogurt sauces. Several vegan choices, plus ask for items to be made without mayonnaise and cream. Comfortable setting with eclectic live music. Also offers a small selection of jams and other  healthy items. Location has been moved to the main road from the original lakeside spot; it is now adjacent to Blind Lemon's. Directions: Main road, on the right when entering the town, one building down from Blind Lemon's, on the corner.
streetAddress: Main road on the right when entering the town
